019d29d8-1e13-7b79-8cd0-8c8be14b7261	2026-03-26 11:12:02.579753+00	2026-03-26 11:12:02.579753+00	\N	019d29d8-1a4a-7d42-9c22-c06ba56ac37a	https://openai.com/index/ai-and-efficiency	AI and efficiency	https://openai.com/index/ai-and-efficiency	We’re releasing an analysis showing that since 2012 the amount of compute needed to train a neural net to the same performance on ImageNet classification has been decreasing by a factor of 2 every 16 months. Compared to 2012, it now takes 44 times less compute to train a neural network to the level of AlexNet (by contrast, Moore’s Law would yield an 11x cost improvement over this period). Our results suggest that for AI tasks with high levels of recent investment, algorithmic progress has yielded more gains than classical hardware efficiency.	OpenAI News	2020-05-05 07:00:00+00	2026-03-26 11:12:02.167097+00				
